Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Macro Expansion Module

Provides advanced macro expansion capabilities including:
- Pattern matching and variable binding
- Template expansion and substitution
- Conditional expansion and branching
- Recursive macro expansion
- Expansion optimization and caching
- Expansion debugging and tracing
- Cross-module expansion support
- AI/agent-friendly expansion tools

Features:
- Advanced pattern matching with constraints
- Template expansion with variable substitution
- Conditional expansion with branching logic
- Recursive macro expansion with cycle detection
- Expansion optimization and performance tuning
- Comprehensive expansion debugging and tracing
- Cross-module expansion with dependency tracking
- AI/agent-friendly expansion development tools
- Production-ready expansion with error handling
:End Note

Note: Expansion Types and Data Structures
Type called "ExpansionEngine":
    context as MacroContext
    pattern_matcher as PatternMatcher
    template_expander as TemplateExpander
    variable_binder as VariableBinder
    expansion_optimizer as ExpansionOptimizer
    debug_tracer as ExpansionDebugTracer
    performance_monitor as ExpansionPerformanceMonitor
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PatternMatcher":
    matchers as Dictionary[String, PatternMatcherFunction]
    constraint_checkers as Dictionary[String, ConstraintCheckerFunction]
    variable_extractors as Dictionary[String, VariableExtractorFunction]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TemplateExpander":
    expanders as Dictionary[String, TemplateExpanderFunction]
    variable_substitutors as Dictionary[String, VariableSubstitutorFunction]
    conditional_processors as Dictionary[String, ConditionalProcessorFunction]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VariableBinder":
    binders as Dictionary[String, VariableBinderFunction]
    validators as Dictionary[String, VariableValidatorFunction]
    transformers as Dictionary[String, VariableTransformerFunction]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExpansionOptimizer":
    optimizers as Dictionary[String, ExpansionOptimizerFunction]
    analyzers as Dictionary[String, ExpansionAnalyzerFunction]
    transformers as Dictionary[String, ExpansionTransformerFunction]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExpansionDebugTracer":
    trace_level as String
    trace_output as List[TraceEntry]
    breakpoints as List[DebugBreakpoint]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExpansionPerformanceMonitor":
    metrics as Dictionary[String, PerformanceMetric]
    thresholds as Dictionary[String, Float]
    alerts as List[PerformanceAlert]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type PatternMatcherFunction is Function that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns Optional[MatchResult]

Type ConstraintCheckerFunction is Function that takes constraint as PatternConstraint and value as Any returns Boolean

Type VariableExtractorFunction is Function that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns List[String]

Type TemplateExpanderFunction is Function that takes template as MacroTemplate and bindings as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[Token]

Type VariableSubstitutorFunction is Function that takes template as String and bindings as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String

Type ConditionalProcessorFunction is Function that takes condition as String and bindings as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean

Type VariableBinderFunction is Function that takes variable as String and value as Any returns Any

Type VariableValidatorFunction is Function that takes variable as String and value as Any returns Boolean

Type VariableTransformerFunction is Function that takes variable as String and value as Any returns Any

Type ExpansionOptimizerFunction is Function that takes expansion as ExpansionResult returns ExpansionResult

Type ExpansionAnalyzerFunction is Function that takes expansion as ExpansionResult returns ExpansionAnalysis

Type ExpansionTransformerFunction is Function that takes expansion as ExpansionResult returns ExpansionResult

Type called "MatchResult":
    matched as Boolean
    bindings as Dictionary[String, Any]
    consumed_tokens as Integer
    remaining_tokens as List[Token]
    confidence as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TraceEntry":
    timestamp as Float
    level as String
    message as String
    data as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DebugBreakpoint":
    condition as String
    action as String
    enabled as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PerformanceMetric":
    name as String
    value as Float
    unit as String
    timestamp as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PerformanceAlert":
    metric as String
    threshold as Float
    current_value as Float
    severity as String
    timestamp as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExpansionAnalysis":
    complexity as Float
    performance_impact as Float
    memory_usage as Float
    optimization_opportunities as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Expansion Engine Functions
Process called "create_expansion_engine" that takes context as MacroContext returns ExpansionEngine:
    Let pattern_matcher be create_pattern_matcher with context as context
    Let template_expander be create_template_expander with context as context
    Let variable_binder be create_variable_binder with context as context
    Let expansion_optimizer be create_expansion_optimizer with context as context
    Let debug_tracer be create_expansion_debug_tracer with context as context
    Let performance_monitor be create_expansion_performance_monitor with context as context
    
    Return ExpansionEngine with:
        context as context
        pattern_matcher as pattern_matcher
        template_expander as template_expander
        variable_binder as variable_binder
        expansion_optimizer as expansion_optimizer
        debug_tracer as debug_tracer
        performance_monitor as performance_monitor
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "expand_macro_with_engine" that takes engine as ExpansionEngine and macro_name as String and input_tokens as List[Token] returns ExpansionResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let trace_entry be TraceEntry with:
            timestamp as start_time
            level as "info"
            message as "Starting macro expansion: " plus macro_name
            data as dictionary containing:
                "macro_name" as macro_name
                "input_token_count" as length of input_tokens
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add trace_entry to engine.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Let macro_def be get_macro with context as engine.context and name as macro_name
        
        If macro_def is None:
            Return ExpansionError with error as "Macro not found: " plus macro_name and details as dictionary containing
        
        Let match_result be match_macro_pattern with engine as engine and pattern as macro_def.pattern and tokens as input_tokens
        
        If not match_result.matched:
            Return ExpansionError with error as "Pattern match failed for macro: " plus macro_name and details as dictionary containing
        
        Let validated_bindings be validate_variable_bindings with engine as engine and bindings as match_result.bindings and macro_def as macro_def
        
        If validated_bindings is None:
            Return ExpansionError with error as "Variable binding validation failed" and details as dictionary containing
        
        Let expanded_tokens be expand_macro_template_with_engine with engine as engine and template as macro_def.template and bindings as validated_bindings
        
        Let expansion_result be ExpansionSuccess with:
            tokens as expanded_tokens
            ast as parse_expanded_tokens with tokens as expanded_tokens and context as engine.context
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing:
                "expansion_time" as get_current_time minus start_time
                "token_count" as length of expanded_tokens
                "variable_count" as length of validated_bindings
        
        Let optimized_result be optimize_expansion with engine as engine and expansion as expansion_result
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let final_trace_entry be TraceEntry with:
            timestamp as end_time
            level as "info"
            message as "Completed macro expansion: " plus macro_name
            data as dictionary containing:
                "macro_name" as macro_name
                "output_token_count" as length of optimized_result.tokens
                "expansion_time" as end_time minus start_time
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add final_trace_entry to engine.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Return optimized_result
        
    Catch error:
        Let error_trace_entry be TraceEntry with:
            timestamp as get_current_time
            level as "error"
            message as "Macro expansion failed: " plus error.message
            data as dictionary containing:
                "macro_name" as macro_name
                "error" as error.message
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add error_trace_entry to engine.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Return ExpansionError with error as error.message and details as dictionary containing

Process called "match_macro_pattern" that takes engine as ExpansionEngine and pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let matcher_function be engine.pattern_matcher.matchers[pattern.syntax] if engine.pattern_matcher.matchers contains pattern.syntax else default_pattern_matcher
        
        Let match_result be matcher_function with pattern as pattern and tokens as tokens
        
        If match_result.matched:
            Let constraint_check_result be check_pattern_constraints with engine as engine and constraints as pattern.constraints and bindings as match_result.bindings
            
            If not constraint_check_result:
                Return MatchResult with:
                    matched as false
                    bindings as dictionary containing
                    consumed_tokens as 0
                    remaining_tokens as tokens
                    confidence as 0.0
                    metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Set match_result.metadata["matching_time"] to end_time minus start_time
        
        Return match_result
        
    Catch error:
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as false
            bindings as dictionary containing
            consumed_tokens as 0
            remaining_tokens as tokens
            confidence as 0.0
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "expand_macro_template_with_engine" that takes engine as ExpansionEngine and template as MacroTemplate and bindings as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[Token]:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let expander_function be engine.template_expander.expanders[template.template_code] if engine.template_expander.expanders contains template.template_code else default_template_expander
        
        Let expanded_tokens be expander_function with template as template and bindings as bindings
        
        Let processed_tokens be process_conditional_sections with engine as engine and template as template and bindings as bindings and base_tokens as expanded_tokens
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let performance_metric be PerformanceMetric with:
            name as "template_expansion_time"
            value as end_time minus start_time
            unit as "seconds"
            timestamp as end_time
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Set engine.performance_monitor.metrics["template_expansion_time"] to performance_metric
        
        Return processed_tokens
        
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "validate_variable_bindings" that takes engine as ExpansionEngine and bindings as Dictionary[String, Any] and macro_def as MacroDefinition returns Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Try:
        Let validated_bindings be dictionary containing
        
        For each variable in macro_def.pattern.variables:
            If bindings contains variable:
                Let value be bindings[variable]
                Let validator_function be engine.variable_binder.validators[variable] if engine.variable_binder.validators contains variable else default_variable_validator
                
                If validator_function with variable as variable and value as value:
                    Let transformer_function be engine.variable_binder.transformers[variable] if engine.variable_binder.transformers contains variable else default_variable_transformer
                    Let transformed_value be transformer_function with variable as variable and value as value
                    Set validated_bindings[variable] to transformed_value
                Otherwise:
                    Return None
            Otherwise:
                Return None
        
        Return validated_bindings
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "optimize_expansion" that takes engine as ExpansionEngine and expansion as ExpansionResult returns ExpansionResult:
    Try:
        Let analysis be analyze_expansion with engine as engine and expansion as expansion
        
        For each optimizer_name in engine.expansion_optimizer.optimizers:
            Let optimizer_function be engine.expansion_optimizer.optimizers[optimizer_name]
            Let optimized_expansion be optimizer_function with expansion as expansion
            
            If optimized_expansion is not expansion:
                Set expansion to optimized_expansion
        
        Return expansion
        
    Catch error:
        Return expansion

Note: Pattern Matching Functions
Process called "create_pattern_matcher" that takes context as MacroContext returns PatternMatcher:
    Let matchers be dictionary containing:
        "function_call" as function_call_pattern_matcher
        "variable_declaration" as variable_declaration_pattern_matcher
        "control_flow" as control_flow_pattern_matcher
        "expression" as expression_pattern_matcher
        "statement" as statement_pattern_matcher
    
    Let constraint_checkers be dictionary containing:
        "type" as type_constraint_checker
        "range" as range_constraint_checker
        "format" as format_constraint_checker
        "custom" as custom_constraint_checker
    
    Let variable_extractors be dictionary containing:
        "identifier" as identifier_variable_extractor
        "literal" as literal_variable_extractor
        "expression" as expression_variable_extractor
    
    Return PatternMatcher with:
        matchers as matchers
        constraint_checkers as constraint_checkers
        variable_extractors as variable_extractors
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "default_pattern_matcher" that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
    Try:
        Let syntax_parts be split_pattern_syntax with pattern as pattern.syntax
        Let bindings be dictionary containing
        Let consumed_count be 0
        Let confidence be 0.0
        
        If length of tokens is less than length of syntax_parts:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        For each index in range from 0 to length of syntax_parts minus 1:
            Let part be syntax_parts[index]
            If index is greater than or equal to length of tokens:
                Return MatchResult with:
                    matched as false
                    bindings as bindings
                    consumed_tokens as consumed_count
                    remaining_tokens as tokens
                    confidence as confidence
                    metadata as dictionary containing
            
            Let token be tokens[index]
            
            If part.startswith with prefix as "$":
                Let variable_name be part.substring with start as 1
                Set bindings[variable_name] to token.value
                Set consumed_count to consumed_count plus 1
                Set confidence to confidence plus 0.8
            Otherwise if part equals token.value:
                Set consumed_count to consumed_count plus 1
                Set confidence to confidence plus 1.0
            Otherwise:
                Return MatchResult with:
                    matched as false
                    bindings as bindings
                    consumed_tokens as consumed_count
                    remaining_tokens as tokens
                    confidence as confidence
                    metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let final_confidence be confidence divided by length of syntax_parts
        
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as true
            bindings as bindings
            consumed_tokens as consumed_count
            remaining_tokens as tokens.slice with start as consumed_count
            confidence as final_confidence
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "pattern_complexity" as length of syntax_parts
                "variable_count" as length of bindings
        
    Catch error:
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as false
            bindings as dictionary containing
            consumed_tokens as 0
            remaining_tokens as tokens
            confidence as 0.0
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "function_call_pattern_matcher" that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
    Try:
        If length of tokens is less than 3:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let function_name_token be tokens[0]
        Let open_paren_token be tokens[1]
        
        If not function_name_token.type equals "identifier":
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        If not open_paren_token.value equals "(":
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let argument_tokens be list containing
        Let consumed_count be 2
        Let paren_depth be 1
        
        For each index in range from 2 to length of tokens minus 1:
            Let token be tokens[index]
            Set consumed_count to consumed_count plus 1
            
            If token.value equals "(":
                Set paren_depth to paren_depth plus 1
            Otherwise if token.value equals ")":
                Set paren_depth to paren_depth minus 1
                If paren_depth equals 0:
                    Break
            
            If paren_depth is greater than 0:
                Add token to argument_tokens
        
        If paren_depth is not equal to 0:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as consumed_count
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let bindings be dictionary containing:
            "function_name" as function_name_token.value
            "arguments" as argument_tokens
        
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as true
            bindings as bindings
            consumed_tokens as consumed_count
            remaining_tokens as tokens.slice with start as consumed_count
            confidence as 0.9
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "function_name" as function_name_token.value
                "argument_count" as length of argument_tokens
        
    Catch error:
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as false
            bindings as dictionary containing
            consumed_tokens as 0
            remaining_tokens as tokens
            confidence as 0.0
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "variable_declaration_pattern_matcher" that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
    Try:
        If length of tokens is less than 4:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let let_token be tokens[0]
        Let variable_name_token be tokens[1]
        Let be_token be tokens[2]
        
        If not let_token.value equals "Let":
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        If not variable_name_token.type equals "identifier":
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        If not be_token.value equals "be":
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let value_tokens be list containing
        Let consumed_count be 3
        
        For each index in range from 3 to length of tokens minus 1:
            Let token be tokens[index]
            If token.type equals "newline" or token.type equals "semicolon":
                Break
            Add token to value_tokens
            Set consumed_count to consumed_count plus 1
        
        Let bindings be dictionary containing:
            "variable_name" as variable_name_token.value
            "value_tokens" as value_tokens
            "declaration_type" as "variable"
        
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as true
            bindings as bindings
            consumed_tokens as consumed_count
            remaining_tokens as tokens.slice with start as consumed_count
            confidence as 0.95
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "variable_name" as variable_name_token.value
                "value_token_count" as length of value_tokens
        
    Catch error:
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as false
            bindings as dictionary containing
            consumed_tokens as 0
            remaining_tokens as tokens
            confidence as 0.0
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "control_flow_pattern_matcher" that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
    Try:
        If length of tokens is less than 2:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let first_token be tokens[0]
        Let control_keywords be list containing "If", "While", "For", "Match", "Try", "Unless"
        
        If not first_token.value in control_keywords:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as 0
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let condition_tokens be list containing
        Let consumed_count be 1
        Let colon_found be false
        
        For each index in range from 1 to length of tokens minus 1:
            Let token be tokens[index]
            Set consumed_count to consumed_count plus 1
            
            If token.value equals ":":
                Set colon_found to true
                Break
            
            Add token to condition_tokens
        
        If not colon_found:
            Return MatchResult with:
                matched as false
                bindings as dictionary containing
                consumed_tokens as consumed_count
                remaining_tokens as tokens
                confidence as 0.0
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Let bindings be dictionary containing:
            "control_type" as first_token.value
            "condition_tokens" as condition_tokens
        
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as true
            bindings as bindings
            consumed_tokens as consumed_count
            remaining_tokens as tokens.slice with start as consumed_count
            confidence as 0.9
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "control_type" as first_token.value
                "condition_token_count" as length of condition_tokens
        
    Catch error:
        Return MatchResult with:
            matched as false
            bindings as dictionary containing
            consumed_tokens as 0
            remaining_tokens as tokens
            confidence as 0.0
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "expression_pattern_matcher" that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
    Note: Expression pattern matcher implementation
    Return MatchResult with:
        matched as false
        bindings as dictionary containing
        consumed_tokens as 0
        remaining_tokens as tokens
        confidence as 0.0
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "statement_pattern_matcher" that takes pattern as MacroPattern and tokens as List[Token] returns MatchResult:
